22 high burden countries remains unknown. Studies on LTBI burden in HCWs in those countries
would provide evidence base to consider necessary guidelines for TB prevention and control.
Future studies should consider using uniformLTBI diagnostic protocols to generate comparable
results across different countries. Appropriate infectioncontrol measures would be the key to pre-
vent nosocomial transmission of TB among HCWs. Future research is neededto identify and test
the effectiveness of feasible and affordable environmental control and respiratory protection mea-
sures in resource-constrainedsettings. HCWs in high burden countries could benefit fromperiod-
ical screening for early detectionof LTBI and monitoring the progression to active TB.
